From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Galileo CSM Workspace <galileo-csm@example.invalid>
Date: Tue, 21 Apr 2026 17:45:00 -0600
Subject: [PATCH] SeaBIOS: use CSM BBS priority for USB storage

In CSM mode, edk2 publishes USB mass-storage media as BBS hard-disk
entries from its already-connected BlockIo handles. SeaBIOS must not run
USB discovery from Legacy16UpdateBbs while edk2 owns the USB controller.

Track SeaBIOS USB drives during normal PrepareToBoot hardware discovery
and reapply the selected CSM BBS priority to the matching INT 13h drive
before the SeaBIOS boot menu and final boot ordering run. The matching key
uses the USB path and LUN so hubs and multi-LUN devices are not collapsed
into one fake disk entry.

Also keep temporary VGA breadcrumbs around the SeaBIOS boot handoff path so
bring-up logs are visible on systems without a working legacy serial port.

